title: Route One Rampage
description: The Route One Rampage marks the University of Maryland Cycling Team's first criterium in ten years. Fast sweeping corners, scenic city views, and vibrant local businesses line the course that winds through Hyattsville, Maryland's historic district.
course: Fast, four-corner, one mile course that traverses quaint neighborhoods, the Hyattsville Downtown area, and takes a dip onto Route One/Baltimore Avenue.
notes:
Collegiate fields are open only to full time collegiate students with
valid USAC Collegiate licenses and full time high school students with
valid USAC Junior licenses.  Jerseys and bibs for all such riders must
feature school names and/or logo, or be generic blank kits;
non‐scholastic club and trade team kits are not permitted.  In
addition, new non‐collegiate women racers with 1‐day or first time
Category 4 licenses may enter Collegiate Women's Intro fields.  USA
Cycling licenses will be available for purchase on‐site.  Consult the ACCC website
at http://www.acccycling.org for more information on
categories, eligibility, licensing, and other general questions
directions: From I-95, continue onto I-95 N/495. Take exit for I-295, then take exit for US-50 W. Follow signs for MD-201 N. Follow 201, and turn left on Annapolis Road, then Right on Baltimore Avenue/Route 1, until reaching Hyattsville.

title: Highway to Hell TT
description: One-mile time trial that climbs the fabled Ilchester Road, a stretch of asphalt known to strike fear in the hearts of those attempting its summit.
course: One-mile hill that tops out at an 18% grade.

title: Gateway Circuit Race
description: Come join the UMD Cycling team for an afternoon of circuit racing at Columbia Gateway Park.
course: The course is a smooth, rolling 2.1 mile circuit and will be fully closed to traffic.
registration: Registration will be available at usacycling.org or on-site starting at 7:00am.  On-site registration will close 30 minutes before each race.  Contact terpscycling@gmail.com with any questions.
notes:
1. The inner lanes of Columbia Gateway Drive will be closed for the race and the centerline rule will be in effect.
2. All USAC rules apply; each rider must present a valid USAC license (annual or one-day)
3. Only Collegiate license holders and juniors in high school may participate in collegiate races.
4. All riders must be wearing either collegiate or generic (no logo) kit.
directions: From exit 41 on I-95, take Rt. 175 West to Columbia Gateway Drive and turn left.  The inner loop of the circuit will be closed to traffic so continue along the road until you arrive at Albert Einstein Drive, where there will be a marshall who will direct you to park.

title: The James P. Bellora Memorial Giro di Coppi
That Dam TT aka The Prettyboy Reservoir Time Trial
description: That Dam TT is the only bicycle race in Baltimore County. The race is a challenging time trial around the Prettyboy Reservoir watershed. All proceeds from the race are donated to the National Multiple Sclerosis Society - Maryland Chapter. The race is a part of the Mid-Atlantic Time Trial Series (MATTS) and is a MABRA BAR race.
course:
The course utilizes a 25K loop with a total elevation gain of just under 3,000 ft. All races are two laps with the exception of juniors which is 1 lap.
Course Route (with elevation profile & turn by turn directions): http://ridewithgps.com/routes/3923346
Lap times will be provided.
registration:
www.bikereg.com/thatdamtt2016
$30 through May 31th; $32.50 through June 30th, $35 until July 21 at 9pm. No registration after this time.
USA Cycling One Day Licenses are required in order to race, if you are not a USA Cycling Annual License Member. One day licenses are available only for Men Cat 5 and Women Cat 4. The charge of the one day license will be charged at checkout. Male one-day licensees may enter the Men's Cat 5 or their appropriate age graded category. Female one day licensees may enter the Women’s Cat 4 or their appropriate age graded category.
Race day sign in will begin at 7:30am.
No day of registration.
notes:
The first racer will start at 9am. Riders will be sent off by category in 30 second intervals.  Exact start times are dependent on the number of registrants, and will be announced on the afternoon of Friday, July 22nd by email to all participants.

Warming up on the course will be prohibited so please bring your trainers. Roads will be open to traffic during the race. Obey all traffic regulations; yellow line rule is in effect and strictly enforced. Littering on the course is prohibited; as we are on the watershed violators will face a race relegation.

Race runs rain or shine. In the event of severe thunderstorms the race will be a 3.5k hill climb. All USAC rules apply. Riders must wear helmets at all times.

Medals for the top 3 in each Category. Prizes may be available. See registration site for latest information.
Podium ceremony and award distribution will begin following the conclusion of all race categories. Winner must be present to claim medals and prizes (if available).
directions: From I-83 take exit 31 for Middletown Road. Proceed west (Left from I-83 North / Right from I-83 South) on Middletown Road for 2.1 miles. Turn left on Rayville Road and parking will be on the left in approximately 0.8 miles. The nearest address is 1717 Rayville Road, Parkton, MD 21120.
